dding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" style=\"width:100%\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td><strong>Test Name</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Observed Value</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Unit</strong></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>R A Factor</td>\n			<td>Negative</td>\n			<td>IU/ml</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>INTERPRETATION:</p>\n\n<p>&lt;20&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; IU/ml&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; =&nbsp; negative<br />\n21-25&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; IU/ml&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; =&nbsp; borderline<br />\n&gt;25&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; IU/ml&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; =&nbsp; positive</p>\n\n<p>COMMENTS</p>\n\n<p>Owing to the nature of RF, an all purpose cut-off value between a positive<br />\n&amp; negative result is considered impractical</p>\n\n<p>Highly elevated values are found mainly in rheumatoid arthritis, whereas nonspecific positive generally give low values.</p>\n',1,1,1,251),(63,'Widal Test',NULL,'<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; WIDAL TEST</strong></p>\n\n<p>Slide agglutination test for Salmonella group of organisms reveal following titers....</p>\n\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" style=\"width:100%\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p><strong>Dilution</strong></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p><strong>1/20</strong></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p><strong>1/40</strong></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p><strong>1/80</strong></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p><strong>1/160</strong></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p><strong>1/320</strong></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>S TYPHI &quot; O &quot;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>{STyphiO1}</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>{STyphiO2}</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>{STyphiO3}</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>{STyphiO4}</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>{STyphiO5}</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>S TYPHI &quot; H &quot;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>{STyphiH1}</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>{STyphiH2}</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>{STyphiH3}</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>{STyphiH4}</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>{STyphiH5}</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>S PARATYPHI&nbsp; &quot; AH &quot;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>{SParaTyphiAH1}</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>{SParaTyphiAH2}</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>{SParaTyphiAH3}</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>{SParaTyphiAH4}</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>{SParaTyphiAH5}</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>S PARATYPHI&nbsp; &quot; BH &quot;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>{SParaTyphiBH1}</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>{SParaTyphiBH2}</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>{SParaTyphiBH3}</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>{SParaTyphiBH4}</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>{SParaTyphiBH5}</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>COMMENT:&nbsp; &nbsp; WIDAL TEST IS &ldquo; NEGATIVE &rdquo;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\nNOTE : Titers of agglutinins to Salmonella antigens , somatic (0) in values upto 40 and for Flagellar (H) in values up to 80 are the endemic titers. Agglutinins may also rise in the serum following Typhoid immunization, past Salmonella &nbsp;infections or infections due to Enterobacteriaceae sharing common antigens. Agglutinins on the other hand may not rise in patients receiving effective antibiotic therapy early in the course of Salmonellosis.<br />\nDiagnostic value of Widal test is increased if rising titers are demonstrated in serial samples. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n',12,1,1,160),(64,'Serum Amylase',NULL,'<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:100%\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td><strong>Test Name</strong></td>\n			<td>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>&nbsp;Result</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Unit</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Normal Values</strong></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Serum Amylase</td>\n			<td style=\"text-align:center\">{AMYLASE}</td>\n			<td>IU/L</td>\n			<td>20.00-80.00 IU/L</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n',1,1,1,241),(65,'Serum Lipase',NULL,'<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:100%\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td><strong>Test Name</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Observed Values</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Unit</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Normal Values</strong></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Serum Lipase</td>\n			<td style=\"text-align:center\">{LIPASE}</td>\n			<td>U/L</td>\n			<td>0-60 U/L</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n',1,1,1,229),(66,'Serum Cholesterol',NULL,'<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:100%\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td><strong>Test Name</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Observed Values</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Unit</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Normal Values</strong></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Serum Cholesterol</td>\n			<td style=\"text-align:center\">{Cholestero}</td>\n			<td>mg/dl</td>\n			<td>130-200 mg/dl</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n',1,1,1,238),(67,'Serum Trigycerides',NULL,'<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:100%\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td><strong>Test Name</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Observed Values</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Unit</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Normal Values</strong></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Serum Trigycerides</td>\n			<td style=\"text-align:center\">{Trigycerides}</td>\n			<td>mg/dl</td>\n			<td>45-160mg/dl</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n',1,1,1,222),(68,'Blood Group RH',NULL,'<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" style=\"width:500px\">\n	<thead>\n		<tr>\n			<th scope=\"col\" style=\"text-align: left;\">Blood Group</th>\n			<th scope=\"col\" style=\"text-align: left;\">Rh (&nbsp;Anti - D)</th>\n		</tr>\n	</thead>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>{ABO}</td>\n			<td>{RHF}</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n',6,1,1,395),(69,'URINE PREGNANCY',NULL,'<p>URINE FOR PREGNANCY&nbsp; :&nbsp; {PREGNANCYT}</p>\n',8,1,1,178),(70,'STOOL ROUTINE EXAMINATION',NULL,'<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" style=\"width:100%\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td><strong>Test Name</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Observed Values</strong></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td><em><strong>Physical Examination</strong></em></td>\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Colour</td>\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>{stool_colo}</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Consistency</td>\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>{Consistenc}</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Mucus</td>\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>{Mucus}</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>PH</td>\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>{SPH}</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td><em><strong>Chemical Examination</strong></em></td>\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Reducing Sugar</td>\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>{RSugar}</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td><em><strong>Microscopic Examination</strong></em></td>\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Pus Cells</td>\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>{PCells}</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>RBCs</td>\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>{sRBC}</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Ova</td>\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>{Ova}</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Cyst</td>\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>{Cyst}</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Fat Globules</td>\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>{FatGlobuli}</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n',3,1,1,213),(71,'TYPHOID IgG &  IgM*,Serum',NULL,'<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" style=\"width:100%\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Test &nbsp;Name</td>\n			<td>Result</td>\n			<td>Unit&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>Bio.Ref.Interval&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>Method</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>TYPHOID, IgG*<br />\n			Sample:Serum</td>\n			<td>{IgG}</td>\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>IMMUNOCHROMATOGRAPHY</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>TYPHOID, IgM*<br />\n			Sample:Serum</td>\n			<td>{IgM}</td>\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>IMMUNOCHROMATOGRAPHY</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>TEST RESULTS&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; : RESULTS &amp; CLINICAL INTERPRETATION &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\nIgM Positive only&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; : Acute Typhoid Fever&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\nIgG &amp; IgM Positive&nbsp; &nbsp;: Acute Typhoid fever(in the middle stage of infection)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\nIgG Positive only&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; : Relapse or reinfection or previous infection(Current fever may not be due to Typhoid) &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\nIgM &amp; IgG Negative&nbsp; : No Typhoid fever &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\nThis test is highly specific in detecting typhoid fever.The 95% sensitivity of the test is much more superior to either Culture or Widal test. Very high positive predictivity value and negative predictivity value of TYPHOID IgG &amp; IgM is also far more superior to both Culture and Widal test. Dot EIA for typhoid fever is the first known qualitative antibody detection test against a specific antigen of Salmonella Typhi,the causative agent for typhoid fever. The test detects both IgG and IgM antibodies separately and simultaneously to indicate the status of acute infection or previous exposure and takes only 1 Hr to complete as compare to longer period in case of both culture and Widal Test.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n</p>\n',12,1,1,188),(72,'MALARIA ANTIGEN',NULL,'<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" style=\"width:100%\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Test &nbsp;Name</td>\n			<td>Result&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>Unit&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>Bio.Ref.Interval</td>\n			<td>Method</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Malarial Antigen<br />\n			P.Vivax *<br />\n			Sample:Blood</td>\n			<td>{MALARIA}</td>\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>IMMUNOCHROMATOGRAPHY</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Malarial Antigen<br />\n			Falciparum*<br />\n			Sample:Blood</td>\n			<td>{MALARIA}</td>\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>IMMUNOCHROMATOGRAPHY</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (*) Test not done under NABL accredited Scope<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n',6,1,1,278),(73,'GAMA GT',NULL,'<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"height:48px; width:585px\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td><strong>Test Name</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Observed Values</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Unit</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Normal Values</strong></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top\">GAMMA GT</td>\n			<td style=\"text-align:center; vertical-align:top\">{GAMAGT}</td>\n			<td style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top\">IU/L</td>\n			<td style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top\"><em>9-52IU/L</em></td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n',1,1,1,346),(74,'CPK-NAC',NULL,'<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"height:48px; width:585px\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td><strong>Test Name</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Observed Values</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Unit</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Normal Values</strong></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top\">CPK-NAC</td>\n			<td style=\"text-align:center; vertical-align:top\">{CPNACK}</td>\n			<td style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top\">IU/L</td>\n			<td style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top\"><em>35-174IU/L</em></td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n',1,1,1,374),(75,'CPK-MB',NULL,'<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"height:48px; width:585px\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td><strong>Test Name</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Observed Values</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Unit</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Normal Values</strong></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top\">CPK-MB</td>\n			<td style=\"text-align:center; vertical-align:top\">{CPKMB}</td>\n			<td style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top\">IU/L</td>\n			<td style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top\"><em>&lt;24 IU/L</em></td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n',1,1,1,375),(76,'PSA(PROSTATIC SPECIFIC ANTIGEN)',NULL,'<p>PSA : &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; {PSA} &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ng/ml</p>\n\n<table style=\"height:183px; width:701px\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>NORMAL RANGE:&nbsp;&nbsp; &lt;40Yrs - 0.21-1.72&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 40-49 Yrs - 0.27-2.19</p>\n\n			<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; 50-59 Yrs - 0.27-3.42&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 60-69 Yrs - 0.22-6.17</p>\n\n			<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &gt;60 Yrs - 0.21-6.77</p>\n\n			<p>SERUM TESTING FOR PSA IS VERY IMPORTANT TOOL TO SCREEN FOR PROSTATE CANCER AND TO MONITOR THERAPY OF THIS DISEASE. PSA IS PROSTATE-SPECIFIC BUT NOT CANCER-SPECIFIC AND APART FROM PROSTATE CANCER INCREASED LEVELS MAY BE FOUND IN BENIGN PROSTATE HYPERTROPHY, PROSTATITIS, INCREASING AGE, ACUTE RETENTION OF URINE, INFECTION AND PROSTATE BIOPSY.</p>\n\n			<p>PSA IS RARELY RAISED IN HEALTY MEN AND IS ABSENT IN NORMAL WOMEN. THERE IS NO PSA PRESENT IN ANYOTHER NORMAL TISSUE FROM MEN OR IN PATIENTS WITH OTHER CANCERS OF THE BREAST, LUNG, COLON, RECTUM, STOMACH PANCREAS OR THYROID.</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n',1,1,1,254),(77,'RETICULOCYTE COUNT',NULL,'<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" style=\"width:100%\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td><strong>Test Name</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Value</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Unit</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Normal Value</strong></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>RETICULOCYTE COUNT</td>\n			<td>{Reticount}</td>\n			<td>%</td>\n			<td>0.20 - 2.00 %</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n',6,1,1,249),(78,'ASO Titer',NULL,'<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"height:48px; width:585px\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td><strong>Test Name</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Observed Values</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Unit</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Normal Values</strong></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top\">ASO</td>\n			<td style=\"text-align:center; vertical-align:top\">{ASO}</td>\n			<td style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top\">IU/mL</td>\n			<td style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top\"><em>&lt;200IU/mL</em></td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n',1,1,1,409),(79,'DENGUE',NULL,'<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" style=\"height:108px; width:551px\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td><strong>TEST</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>RESULT</strong></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Dengue Ns1</td>\n			<td>{DNS1}</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Dengue IgM</td>\n			<td>{DIGM}</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Dengue IgG</td>\n			<td>{DIGG}</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>Dengue viruses is a flavivirus found largely in areas of the tropic and sub-tropics. There are four distinct but antigeniclly related serotypes of dengue viruses, and transmission is by mosquito, principally Aedes aegypti and Aedes albopictus.</p>\n\n<p>Primary infection with dengue virus results in a self-limitig disease characterized by mild to high fever lasting 3 to 7 days, sever headache with pain behind the eyes, muscle and joint pain, rash and vomiting. Secondary infection is the more common from of the disease in many parts of Southeast Asia and South America; IgM antibodies are not detectable until 5-10 days in case of primary dengueinfection and until 4-5 days in secondary infection after the onset of illness. IgG appear after 14 days and persist for life in case primary infection and rise within 1-2 days after the onset of symptoms in secondary infection.</p>\n\n<p>Primary dengue virus infection is characterized by elevatons in specific NS1 antigen levels 0 to 9 days after the onset of symptoms; this generally presists upto 15 days. Earler diagnosis of Dengue reduces risk of compliation such as DHF or DSS, especially in countries where dengue is endemic.</p>\n',12,1,1,366),(80,'Direct Coombs Test',NULL,'<p>DCT&nbsp; :&nbsp; {DCT}</p>\n',12,1,1,362),(81,'Stool for Occult Blood',NULL,'<h3>Stool for Occult Blood&nbsp; :&nbsp; {occult}</h3>\n',3,1,1,215),(82,'Bile Salt',NULL,'',8,1,1,0),(83,'BILE PIGMENT',NULL,'',8,1,1,0),(84,'Hepatitics  